From: Christian Kastner <ckk@debian.org>
Date: Sun, 31 May 2026 10:14:26 +0200
Subject: cmake: Install impls to private directories

Upstream has factored out utility functionality into shared objects so
that it can be used from multiple frontends. Nothing outside of
upstream's utilities should use this (for now), so make these -impl.so
objects private.

Forwarded: not-needed
---
 tools/batched-bench/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 tools/cli/CMakeLists.txt           | 2 +-
 tools/completion/CMakeLists.txt    | 2 +-
 tools/fit-params/CMakeLists.txt    | 2 +-
 tools/llama-bench/CMakeLists.txt   | 2 +-
 tools/perplexity/CMakeLists.txt    | 2 +-
 tools/quantize/CMakeLists.txt      | 2 +-
 tools/server/CMakeLists.txt        | 2 +-
 8 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/batched-bench/CMakeLists.txt b/tools/batched-bench/CMakeLists.txt
index f6ed257..65df609 100644
--- a/tools/batched-bench/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tools/batched-bench/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -9,7 +9,7 @@ target_include_directories(${TARGET} PUBLIC ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR})
 target_link_libraries(${TARGET} PUBLIC llama-common llama ${CMAKE_THREAD_LIBS_INIT})
 
 if(LLAMA_TOOLS_INSTALL)
-    install(TARGETS ${TARGET} LIBRARY)
+    install(TARGETS ${TARGET} LIBRARY DESTINATION ${LLAMA_LIB_INSTALL_DIR})
 endif()
 
 # llama-batched-bench executable
